caption: Had an amazing time. Drinks are on point, the Food is delicious! The staff goes above and beyond!
Good food, great drinks. Nice addition to the neighborhood.
Lovely service, excellent cocktails, super delicious food and a chill vibe. A great addition to the neighborhood. Will definitely be back!

Delicious cocktails and good vibes. The “tater tots” were way better than advertised, and were yummy little potato pillows with a crispy outside topped with cotija cheese and an amazing crema sauce. So much better than I expected!
Inventive cocktails and great Hawaiian fusion food. The elotes we're insane, as were the nachos. Nice outdoor seating, too!

Absolutely extraordinary food. The fried chicken sandwich is perfectly battered and just spicy enough without sacrificing flavor. The tuna poke bowl is as fresh as you'll find at any sushi joint in the neighborhood. The tater tots should go by another name, because they are too fancy, too meaty with potatoes to be given such a pedestrian name. The cocktails are crafted within an inch of their lives, and the malasada dessert is light and flaky while also being devilishly decadent. One of the best meals to be had in Park Slope right now!
Tasty Hawaiian tacos, poke and cocktails with a nice outdoor patio off the beaten path near the train. 🤙

I give two stars because when it finally did come it was pretty good. Cocktails are just okay. Probably won't go back.  Waited for over an hour to get our food which would have been "okay" if the waitress had better communicated the situation. Once the food did come out she offered us free wine which we didn't take but didn't compensate us in any other way for our time spent there waiting for the meals.

The only reason I am giving 3 stars and not less is because this place used to be great, for dining in and ordering from. Tonight was a totally different story.  Ordered the burger, which has always been delicious, but tonight NOTHING was cooked. The fries were soggy, they didn't look like they were even cooked and the burger was raw, it was supposed to be medium. We ordered 2 and both orders were a disaster.  What a waste of $50, won't be ordering again.

Been here a dozen times and the food is consistently good. The pizza is better elsewhere but all the pastas, entrees, and salads are solid. My personal favorites are the Bolognese and the Cavolo salad.  The bar is very well stocked, wines are hit or miss like most places.  It's a small place typically with a single server so service can be a little wonky depending on who is working.

Good food and really nice outdoor seating. The pizza was delicious, but the hummus was store-bought, not made in the house. The truffle French fries are also really tasty - and I don’t normally find French fries appealing at all. Great for a night out with friends! Not crowded on Sunday night is a total plus
The drink was made of pure Barney flesh
Very good food and cocktails can be found here. Pleasant staff.
Excellent service!
(Translated by Google) Nice terrace to sit outside, and great food.  (Original) Schöne Terrasse um draußen zu sitzen, und hervorragendes Essen.
Go for the drinks not the food. Pasta wasn’t fresh at all but the cocktails were delicious
Great cocktail and wine options (they also have beer). A good selection of salads, pizza, and pasta. The atmosphere is lovely with an old and quaint feel. They also have a patio.
Good food and wine selection.

(Translated by Google) Despite the name, it is a eatery and we were just allowed to settle for a beer. Not strange operation.  (Original) På trods af navnet er det et spisested og vi fik kun lige akkurat lov til at nøjes med en øl. Ikke rar betjening.
My wife and I have been there quite a few times... Great pizza, great wine, great place !
Beautiful space, lovely old bar area, tin ceiling and walls. Lovely delicious fresh food, great drinks and reasonably priced. Never too busy for brunch. Outdoor space too!
Nasty
Good mid-priced Italian joint with a very passable wine selection.  My party managed to mix it up nicely with various pastas and pizzas ordered and nobody had a single complaint.
A decent meal, at a decent price. Friendly service.
The octopus and truffle fries were really good, and i loved my drink! Our server was also very attentive

Good spot for happy hour and the nicest option in the immediate vicinity. Also very cozy with a broad menu that has something for everyone. Service is always fast. Great spot for before an event at the Bell House. Nice wine selection and feel good beers make this a good regular spot.

Food was fine but service was god awful. The girl had an attitude, tried to convince us that antipasti is “not an appetizer” when she forgot to bring out our hummus, still charged us for it even when we said we no longer wanted it — the place was almost empty but we still had to practically wave her down to get more water. Bye.
Great food, attentive service, and great beer.
Good italian fare, great bar
Neighborhood staple. Great staff!

My wife and I hosted a wedding rehearsal dinner at Bar Tano on a Saturday night in early October. Working with the staff to schedule the dinner, decide whether to order off the menu or specify a menu and, generally, making the arrangements was easy with excellent communications by their staff.  We had never been there before and were surprised to see how small the restaurant is but extremely pleased that about half of the restaurant had been set aside for our party of 15 on a busy Saturday night.  The service we received was excellent and the food was very good. Everyone enjoyed the appetizers and the main courses which ranged from Italian food to steak. My son's father-in-law noted that he had one of the best rib-eye steaks he'd ever had.  We decided to provide some bottles of wine for the table and the server's suggestions for both red and white were also very good. It seems they have a very good wine list.  All in all, it was a perfect and comfortable evening at Bar Tano and served as a fantastic beginning to our wedding festivities.
The food was fine but the service was really awful or rather clueless.  Disappointed because this place is a 2 minute walk for us.
We got here randomly, we don’t live in the neighborhood but we were around and decided to come in for dinner. Is one of the best Italians we’ve had in NYC. We will be back for sure!
Some of the best Italian food I've had in the city... definitely the best I've tried in Brooklyn so far!

I’m a local and have had decent food here in the past, but am really disappointed with the way they seat people- not a first come first serve place.  I came during dinner for a table for two before the big dinner time rush and was told to wait by the bar until my friend arrived. I thought this was weird because I had a party of two, not a group and the place was half empty. Several people came in while I waited the 5 mins it took for my friend to arrive.  When I told the hostess we were all present, she pointed to the tiny ledge behind the bar, which she acknowledged would be uncomfortable and told us we could sit there because there weren’t any tables for two people available or sit outside where it was raining. Meanwhile there were two tables for four free. This is just unfair and it’s not a good way to do business when you start to see customers as seats to fill and not as people.  Understand the desire to maximize the space but you shouldn’t do it at the cost of tangible customers who are actually there and waiting before everyone else, especially ghost tables of four who don’t even exist yet.
Great food and wine. Great spot for a date, catching up with a friend or a family night.
Excellent Thursday Happy Hour Bartender  & Very Welcoming Regular Crowd!... Beautiful Random Time.
This is a wonderful restaurant.  Good food, great service, and a really beautiful bar.  Great place to have a meal before an event at Bell House.
Good food. Interesting selection of beer. Good avacado toast.
amazing
Great food and atmosphere.

We have tried to like this place so much, but unfortunately it just keeps letting us down. First off, the location is good, the food and drinks seem good in theory, and the huge zinc bar top is amazing. It's one of the few zinc bars still around, and it has to be one of the longest zinc bar tops out there.  My wife and I visited once long ago, and had a decent experience. But then, we tried on two separate occasions to visit, and they were for some reason closed, even though their posted hours said they were open. The final straw was a recent visit with my buddy.  We were in on an afternoon, close to when they opened, and the bar was basically empty. I don't need to go through all the details, but the service was shockingly bad. The girl working was very very nice, and tried her best, but she obviously had had zero training. She really had no idea what she was doing, to the point of not even knowing what the shot of fernet and a peroni happy hour special meant. I mean, it's on the menu as a special! How does a bartender not know what this is? It was super disappointing, and I felt bad for her, but we won't be back.
This place is AWESOME. Priced reasonably and call them about happy hour.  Calamari great, pastas delicious.  Just a great fun hidden gem.
Nice staff, good food, great design and good outdoor seating. Could have a more diverse menu.

We came here for dinner before going to a show at The Bell House. We had a wonderful dining experience! The atmosphere was intimate and unique. The cocktails were well balanced, and our bruschetta and pizzas were incredible! We were very sad that we couldn’t take our leftover pizza with us because we were going to a show.
Excellent simple italian spot. Outdoor seating is a big plus. Pasta was creative and tasty, pizza as thin crust, crispy and ingredients were well paired.
great food, not fast lunch service on weekdays for dine-in
Great cocktails. Nice service.
Great for lunch
Delicious panini and the house made chips were awesome. Erin is an amazing server !
Nice cozy bar

Great food. I like the lunch and brunch specials. They don't serve the same food in the evening. Waiters are super slow though. Sometimes I'm waiting for someone to take my order for over a minute and I'm the only one in the restaurant. But I can look past that when I bite into the food.

This place has sadly gone downhill. My husband and I live right down the street from Bar Tano and we used to LOVE going there. We were regulars at the bar, and we enjoyed eating dinner there. The old manager (forgot his name) was so friendly and truly cared about the restaurant and it's guests. Then the management changed......and now the food, drinks, and ESPECIALLY the service have gone downhill. We will now walk out of our way to south slope for good Italian food. Disappointing. The last straw was when we sat at the bar for 15 mins without even being acknowledged (like just a "Hello, I'll be right with you") from the bartender. Unacceptable.
Small place, great atmosphere, good food and service
One of the few places around here to get a decent meal.
Very unfriendly staff

This is a fantastic restaurant with reasonable prices, great fresh food and decor that makes you think you are in the heart of Italy, not park slope. The original tin ceiling from the 1930s makes this place popular for movies and weddings and other special occasions. Have tried everything vegetarian on the menu and lots of specials and honestly, have never had a bad meal here. Enjoy!
Eat everything here. Seriously eat everything. It's all amazing.
Delicious bruschettas
Delicious
Went on Christmas Eve. They treated us like family.

Stumbled across this cute bar/restaurant and expected just a quick bite. I was pleasantly surprised by the authenticity of each Italian dish and the welcoming atmosphere. We had pasta dishes - cooked al dente to the T, fresh cheese, and high quality vegetables and meat. Great beer list as well. Would recommend this spot for a casual meal or get together with friends!
Fine pasta, grilled bread, and a variety of amaros.  Nice place.
Great brunch and dinner experience. Food is always good. A little off the Park Slope beaten path so easier to get seating. Service is great. Eat there often and have never been disappointed.
Great. Came for brunch on Sunday. Low key, no fuss. We both had salads, one with salmon, the other with chicken. Fresh and delicious.

It's saying something when an Italian restaurant can't muster up something resembling a half decent carbonara. What I got was scalding hot burnt-tasting cheese sauce over stodgy pasta. Absolutely nothing like a real carbonara. I couldn't taste anything other than cheese. Very disappointing.
Service, food, drinks... Everything was excellent! I will surely go again to this place next time I'm in Brooklyn.

we had dinner there this week and it was excellent, 5 stars! we started w pork meatballs over polenta and spinach as well as the 3 of the chesse based brushetta: both choices were right on the mark; next was pasta, i had the carbonera and my friend had the bolognese: both top-notch; the service was friendly and maybe too efficient.  i highly recommend bartano.  joel from the heights

Good food, friendly people, decent drinks. The food is actually better than the drinks, which for a place with "Bar" in the title is a little weird, but it's great to have fresh, delicious Italian in the neighborhood.
Great food, excellent service, and good beer. We were pleasantly surprised by the whole meal.

I discovered this little gem of a cafe this afternoon, after a class at the Brooklyn Art Space down the street, and ended up enjoying a very lovely brunch. The service was attentive, the food delicious, and the decor wonderful. It looks like a little Italian bar out of the 1920's, with ornate plaster walls and ceilings, dark painted wood, and lots of glass and mirrors. I really enjoyed the rigatoni with sun-dried tomatoes, gorgonzola and capers. The prices are moderate, and the sun streaming in through the windows this afternoon made it the perfect place to sip an Irish coffee and linger over a book. If only it were closer to upper Manhattan, I'd come here often.

Excellent food,service and decor. All their entres,soups and desserts are delicious. They serve a fantastic mojito drink. The service is promt and the servers are very friendly. Their portions are large and the presentations enticing. It's a great place to take family and friends. We patronize often. It's become our most favorite place to eat out. We love Bar Tano.
